2ï¸âƒ£ Software Quality â€“ Meaning & Importance
What is Software Quality?
Software quality means:
Software does what user expects
Works correctly, securely, and efficiently
Is easy to use and maintain

Key Quality Attributes:
Functionality
Reliability
Usability
Performance
Security
Maintainability

ğŸ§  Easy line for exams/interviews:
Software quality ensures customer satisfaction by delivering defect-free and reliable software.

3ï¸âƒ£ STLC (Software Testing Life Cycle)
STLC defines testing activities step-by-step.

STLC Phases:
Requirement Analysis
Test Planning
Test Case Design
Test Environment Setup
Test Execution
Test Cycle Closure

ğŸ“Œ Why STLC matters?
Proper planning
Less confusion
Better defect tracking
Higher quality product

4ï¸âƒ£ V-Model (Verification & Validation Model)
What is V-Model?
It shows development & testing run in parallel.

Development Phase	Testing Phase
Requirements	Acceptance Testing
System Design	System Testing
Architecture Design	Integration Testing
Coding	Unit Testing

ğŸ“Œ Key Point:
Testing starts early, not after coding
ğŸ§  Exam Tip:
V-Model reduces late defect detection.

